9. Coding Question: Find Customers Who Ordered More Than Once

Sample Data:

CREATE TABLE CustomerOrders (OrderID INT PRIMARY KEY, CustomerID INT, OrderDate DATE);

INSERT INTO CustomerOrders (OrderID, CustomerID, OrderDate) VALUES

(101, 1, '2024-01-05'),

(102, 2, '2024-02-10'), (103, 1, '2024-02-15'), (104, 3, '2024-03-20'), (105, 1, '2024-03-25');

Question:

Write an SQL query to find customers who have placed more than one order.

10. Explain ACID properties in SQL and how they ensure data consistency.
